verbose_text: (B) For cases where two reasons F 1 and F 2 derive from the same end : F 1 is a stronger reason than F 2 (for a subject S) iff F 1 raises the probability of the end to which the act for which it is a reason is conducive to a value higher than F 2.
evidence: subject S) iff F 1  raises the probability of the end
